                        "displayName": "Stefan Gehrig",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Should rather be an Zend_Auth_Adapter_Ldap issue.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=sgehrig",
                        "name": "sgehrig",
                        "displayName": "Stefan Gehrig",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-05T08:42:04.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-05T08:42:04.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35798",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=sgehrig",
                        "name": "sgehrig",
                        "displayName": "Stefan Gehrig",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Are you using the membership-feature (using the {{group}}-setting not being {{null}})?\r\nIf so the auth-adapter must rebind with the user given in the adapter options to prevent access restriction problems.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=sgehrig",
                        "name": "sgehrig",
                        "displayName": "Stefan Gehrig",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-05T08:44:49.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-05T08:44:49.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35799",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=primolan",
                        "name": "primolan",
                        "displayName": "Rodrigo Novelo Primolan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Would be these options?\r\n\r\n{code}\r\nZend_Auth_Adapter_Ldap (line 380)\r\n\r\n        $adapterOptions = array(\r\n            'group'       => null,\r\n            'groupDn'     => $ldap->getBaseDn(),\r\n            'groupScope'  => Zend_Ldap::SEARCH_SCOPE_SUB,\r\n            'groupAttr'   => 'cn',\r\n            'groupFilter' => 'objectClass=groupOfUniqueNames',\r\n            'memberAttr'  => 'uniqueMember',\r\n            'memberIsDn'  => true\r\n        );\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nI didn't know about those options. So I guess group may still {code}null{code}.\r\n\r\nMy login is working perfectly, as my searches. The only \"problem\" is that before every search I must bind again.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=primolan",
                        "name": "primolan",
                        "displayName": "Rodrigo Novelo Primolan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-05T09:14:42.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-05T09:14:42.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35801",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=sgehrig",
                        "name": "sgehrig",
                        "displayName": "Stefan Gehrig",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The options should be fine. Could you please provide some sample code of what you're doing so that I can build a test-case to replicate your issue?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=sgehrig",
                        "name": "sgehrig",
                        "displayName": "Stefan Gehrig",
                        "active": true
